{"id":1212188137,"question_id":3363,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"2 months, 2 weeks","timestamp":1711250962,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"216 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1212188137/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Most Frequent IDs","memory":"93.3 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public long[] mostFrequentIDs(int[] nums, int[] freq) {\n        \n        int len = nums.length;\n        \n        Map<Integer, Long> map = new HashMap<>(); // id, freq\n        \n        TreeMap<Long, Set<Integer>> tmap = new TreeMap<>(); // freq , List<id>\n        \n        long[] res = new long[len];\n        \n        for(int i=0; i<len; i++){\n            \n            int id = nums[i];\n            long f = (long)freq[i];\n            \n            \n            if(map.containsKey(id)){\n                long old_f = map.get(id);\n            \n                tmap.getOrDefault(old_f, new HashSet<>()).remove(id);\n                if(tmap.getOrDefault(old_f, new HashSet<>()).size()==0) tmap.remove(old_f);\n            }\n            \n            \n            map.put(id, map.getOrDefault(id, 0L)+f);\n            \n            long new_f = map.get(id);\n            tmap.putIfAbsent(new_f, new HashSet<>());\n            tmap.get(new_f).add(id);\n            \n            res[i] = tmap.lastKey();\n            \n            \n        }\n        \n        return res;\n            \n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"most-frequent-ids","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
